==Turkish==
===Etymology===
From {{inh|tr|ota|یرمك|tr=yermek|t=loathe; blame}}, from {{inh|tr|trk-pro|*jẹr-||to hate}}.<ref>{{R:tut-pro:SDM}}: [http://starling.rinet.ru/cgi-bin/response.cgi?single=1&basename=%2fdata%2falt%2faltet&text_number=2598&root=config “*ǯḕri”]</ref> Cognate with {{cog|kk|жеру}}, {{cog|otk|tr=yer-|t=to hate, dispraise}},<ref>[http://www.nisanyansozluk.com/?k=yer-&lnk=1 "yer-"] - nişanyansözlük</ref>
, {{cog|sah|сир||to disdain, dislike, reject}}.
===Verb===
{{tr-verb|yerer}}
# {{lb|tr|transitive}} to [[run down]], point out the [[fault]]s of, [[criticize]], speak [[ill]] of
# {{lb|tr|transitive}} to [[satirize]]; to [[deride]]
# {{lb|tr|transitive}} to [[disapprove]]; to [[condemn]]
